 
  
 <p><strong>Description  of the postdoctoral position</strong></p>
<p>The candidate is expected to carry  out research on topics related to &ldquo;teacher&rsquo;s policy, teaching practices and pre  and in- service teacher education&rdquo; at the Center for Advanced Research in  Education (CIAE) of the Institute of Education at the Universidad de Chile. Specifically,  the candidate might work on issues related to teachers&rsquo; performance, career,  effectiveness, formal and school-based learning, as well as comparative  teacher-related policies. The candidate is expected to collaborate actively with researchers in this area and other related ones  in CIAE.  Our Research Center is located in the city of Santiago, the capital of Chile.</p>
<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>A PhD degree in Education, Sociology, Economics or a related discipline  awarded between September, 2019 and March 30, 2021. </li>
  <li>Relevant scientific  publications.</li>
  <li>Strong teamwork and  communication skills.</li>
  <li>Experience in interdisciplinary  collaboration is highly desirable.</li>
  <li>Fluency in Spanish is desirable  but not mandatory.</li>
  <li>Strong academic education and  advanced skills in qualitative and/or quantitative education research methods.</li>
</ul>

 <p><strong>Research proposal:</strong><br>
The candidate must present a brief research proposal (not longer than  3,000 words) in line with the research areas described above. The proposal must  describe the aim of the research, methodology, research plan and its  contribution to the education field.</p>
 <p><strong>Documents needed for the  application</strong></p>
<ul>
   <li>Curriculum vitae, including  publication list</li>
   <li>A letter stating reasons for  applying (up to 2 pages)</li>
   <li>Two recent reference letters,  focusing on the candidate&rsquo;s academic work and research skills as well as  experience in collaborative work.</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>Information about the position</strong></p>
 <ul>
   <li>The candidate will be fully  dedicated to research in an active research-oriented environment, with no  teaching duties</li>
   <li>Expected Duration: One year. After this year, the candidate is expected  to apply for external funding. The Chilean National Agency of Research and  Development (ANID) holds a yearly public competitive call for postdoctoral scholarships.</li>
   <li>Financial information</li>
   <ul>
     <li>Monthly salary: 1,800,000  Chilean pesos (before taxes; approx. 2,700 US dollars)<a href="#_ftn1" name="_ftnref1" title=""> </a></li>
     <li>Flight ticket (round trip) to  Santiago, Chile will be covered </li>
   </ul>
 </ul>
	<p><strong>The application process will be opened until March 30, 2021.</strong></p>
